        <p>Li-Fi, short for "Light Fidelity," is a cutting-edge wireless communication technology that utilizes visible light to transmit data. Conceived by Harald Haas, a professor at the University of Edinburgh, Li-Fi represents a promising alternative to traditional radio frequency (RF) communication methods such as Wi-Fi.</p>

        <p>At its core, Li-Fi leverages the rapid flickering of LED (Light Emitting Diode) bulbs to transmit binary data...</p>

